text: more notes to future Josh: L0B and L0R return the same setpoints because this isn't set up in ramp/soak mode with multiple segments. there is only one setpoint for each zone so current set point always going to be equal to setpoint
also note: when setting variables in the pid ie L3b030003000300030003000300 there is some garbage echoed back (thanks OMEGA). be sure to flush your input buffer before you read again
last note: timing is a little weird. when chunking commands together pause for a second between commands
